", "about": "

Welcome to Halley House, Your Nashville Oasis!

Location: Discover the heartbeat of Nashville in the vibrant Jolene building, just across the Cumberland River from downtown. Immerse yourself in the Music City's essence, with easy access to restaurants, shopping, bars, wineries, and nightlife. A short walk or rideshare away, explore musical concerts, museums, historic exhibits, and iconic attractions like the Grand Ole Opry, Centennial Park, and the Adventure Science Center. Local cafes and restaurants within walking distance provide delicious options for every meal.

Outdoor Features: As the sun sets, unwind on the rooftop terrace with a cocktail by the inviting firepit, enjoying the breathtaking views and cool evening breezes.

Indoor Amenities: Start your day at the nearby coffee shop, then return to Halley House's cozy interior. The open floor plan ensures connection and comfort, featuring a living room with a smart TV, a sleek modern kitchen with stainless steel appliances, and a dining table for 4.

Sleeping Arrangements: This home comfortably sleeps 6 guests. Bedroom #1 boasts a king-size bed, while Bedroom #2 offers a king-size bed and an ensuite bathroom with a glass walk-in shower. A queen-size sleeper sofa in the living room provides additional sleeping space. An additional full guest bathroom with a shower/tub combo is also available.

Important Notes:

  • Washer and dryer in the home.
  • Garage parking for 1 vehicle with overflow parking on the street (first come, first served).

Local Attractions: Halley House is ideally located just 2 miles from downtown Nashville, the heart of \"Music City.\" Explore endless shopping, dining, and the exciting nightlife that makes Nashville unique. Dive into the rich musical history with attractions like honky-tonks, the Johnny Cash Museum, Music Row, the Grand Ole Opry House, the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum, and Ryman Auditorium.

Your Nashville adventure begins at Halley House, where comfort meets the soul of the city!

", "about": "

Location: Discover Rhapsody, a chic and stylish home located in the Cleveland Park section of East Nashville, less than 3 miles from the heart of downtown. This prime location offers the perfect blend of convenience and comfort, allowing you to explore the vibrant city while returning to a peaceful retreat.

Indoor Amenities: Upon arrival, you'll be welcomed by a bright and airy interior adorned with sophisticated furnishings. The living space boasts a Smart TV, electric fireplace, and a spacious sectional that can accommodate 3 guests as a sofa sleeper. The open kitchen features white shaker cabinets, granite countertops, and a full suite of stainless steel appliances. It's fully equipped with a blender, coffee maker, toaster, and other kitchen essentials. The center island with 4 stools is ideal for entertaining, while the dining table comfortably seats 6-7 guests.

Sleeping Arrangements: Rhapsody comfortably sleeps up to 10 guests in the following accommodations:

  • Bedroom #1 (Primary Suite): King bed, Smart TV, and en-suite bathroom with a double vanity and walk-in shower featuring custom marble tiling.
  • Bedroom #2 and Bedroom #3: Queen-size beds, sharing a Jack and Jill style bathroom with dual sinks and a shower/tub combo.
  • Bedroom #4 (Office Space): Twin-size futon that folds down.

In addition to the full bathrooms, a half bathroom is conveniently located on the first floor.

Outdoor Features: The property offers a fenced-in backyard with enticing amenities, including a gas grill, fire pit with seating, and a well-maintained lawn. Please note that the backyard is shared with a long-term renter in the separate back unit.

Local Attractions: From East Nashville's cafes and mom-and-pop shops to the bustling downtown, you'll have easy access to a variety of dining and entertainment options. Downtown Nashville, with its bars, restaurants, shops, and live music venues, is just a 7-minute drive away. Don't miss the Country Music Hall of Fame, Johnny Cash Museum and Cafe, and The Nashville Farmers Market to immerse yourself in the local food and music culture. If you're looking for a change of pace, the Grand Ole Opry is a 14-minute drive, and the Belle Meade Historic Site and Winery are less than 25 minutes away.

Important Notes:

  • Please be aware that the backyard is shared with a long-term renter in the separate back unit.

Location: Discover this charming bungalow located just a short 10-minute drive from downtown Nashville. Situated in the trendy east Nashville district, you'll have bars, dining, and shopping within walking distance, making it an ideal vacation spot.

Outdoor Features: Enjoy the enchanting curb appeal with a white picket fence lining the front yard. Relax in the front porch or step into the back patio with seating for morning coffee and al fresco dining.

Indoor Amenities: This two-level home offers a laid-back cottage vibe with neutral decor and hardwood floors throughout. The living room features a Smart TV, perfect for entertainment. The updated kitchen is a chef's paradise with granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, and ample counter space. A mudroom keeps your belongings secure and out of sight.

Sleeping Arrangements: The home sleeps up to 9 guests comfortably with 4 bedrooms and 2.5 bathrooms. The first floor includes a master bedroom and an office space with a king-sized bed. The second floor offers 2 bedrooms, a loft space with additional sleeping, and a full bathroom. The stately master bedroom has a King bed and en-suite, while Bedroom #2 features a Queen bed. Upstairs, Bedroom #3 has two twin beds, and Bedroom #4 offers a full bed.

Important Notes:

  • Parking is available on the street and off the private alley behind the house.
  • A washer and dryer are available for guest use.
  • NO pets and NO smoking are allowed. A $300 fine will be issued for any violation of these rules.
  • Quiet hours are between 10:00 pm and 7:00 am. Parties and loud noise are not permitted.

Local Attractions: Explore downtown Nashville's excitement, bars, restaurants, and more, just a short drive away. The trendy east Nashville district offers local delights within walking distance.

", "about": "

Location: Welcome to Record Retreat, a luxurious three-bedroom vacation home located just 9 minutes away from Downtown Nashville. This prime location allows you to immerse yourself in all the local attractions that Nashville has to offer. Additionally, you'll find the Nashville Farmers Market a mere 6 minutes away and the beautiful Bicentennial Capitol Mall State Park, rich in Nashville history, just 7 minutes away.

Outdoor Features: Record Retreat offers a serene and private rooftop deck on the fourth level, where you can escape to the clouds and enjoy breathtaking views. This outdoor oasis comes equipped with a smart TV and fun outdoor games, providing the perfect setting for relaxation and entertainment.

Indoor Amenities: The main living area, situated on the 2nd level, boasts a fully equipped kitchen, a spacious 6-person dining area, and a bright and welcoming living room. For coffee lovers, there's a Keurig available to kickstart your mornings. You can also enjoy the serene private balcony on this level. Additionally, a half-bath is conveniently located on this floor.

Sleeping Arrangements:

  • Bedroom #1 (Master Suite on the 3rd level): This room features a comfortable king bed, a smart TV, and an en-suite bathroom with double vanity sinks, a walk-in shower, and a walk-in closet.
  • Bedroom #2 (1st Level Guest Bedroom): This cozy room offers a queen bed, a smart TV, and an en-suite bathroom with a standing shower.
  • Bedroom #3 (3rd Level): Perfect for families or groups, this room includes two bunk beds with twin beds on top of full beds, accommodating up to 6 guests. It also features a smart TV and an en-suite bathroom with a shower and tub.

Important Notes:

  • Adjacent to the master suite on the 3rd level, there's a spiral staircase leading to the 2nd level balcony.
  • A private washer and dryer are conveniently located in the main living area.
  • The property includes a 1-car garage for your convenience.
  • A quaint backyard area is available on the 1st level.

Experience the best of Nashville from the comfort of Record Retreat. Book your stay today for an unforgettable vacation in the heart of Music City!

", "about": "

Location: Welcome to Chic Escape, a delightful abode located less than 2 miles from Downtown Nashville. Situated in a charming neighborhood, this retreat offers the perfect blend of tranquility and proximity to Music City's popular attractions, making it an ideal choice for your Nashville adventure.

Outdoor Features: While exploring the quaint neighborhood, you'll find numerous cafes, restaurants, bars, and entertainment venues within a convenient 10-minute walk. For those interested in the history and craft of southern distilleries, both Nelson’s Green Brier Distillery and Corsair Distillery & Taproom are less than a mile away. Art enthusiasts can visit the gallery at Fisk University, just 0.4 miles away. Don't miss the renowned Nashville Farmers Market, 1.4 miles away, where you can stock up on fresh produce and enjoy crafts, classes, and chef demos.

Indoor Amenities: As you step inside Chic Escape, you'll be greeted by a bright and spacious open-concept main floor. The living room offers ample seating and a Smart TV for your entertainment. The well-equipped kitchen features a full suite of stainless steel appliances, perfect for preparing southern-style dishes. Beautiful honey-planked ceilings add character and warmth to this charming space, and the center island with 2 stools provides additional prep space or a gathering spot for guests.

Sleeping Arrangements: Chic Escape comfortably accommodates up to 5 guests with two private bedrooms on the 2nd floor and a futon in the living room. Each space is furnished with cozy linens to ensure a restful stay. Bedroom #1 features a Queen bed, and Bedroom #2 offers a King bed. These bedrooms are connected by a Jack-and-Jill style bathroom with a shower/tub combo. Additionally, there is a convenient half bathroom on the main floor for guests' use.

Important Notes: If you plan to bring a pet, please note that the pet fee is not included in the total price. An additional pet fee of $35 per day per pet will be applied after booking is complete. The unit allows a maximum of 2 pets.

Local Attractions: Beyond the immediate neighborhood, downtown Nashville awaits with its historical sites, renowned restaurants, vibrant honky tonks, and more. Chic Escape offers you the perfect starting point to explore the best that Music City has to offer.

With Blue Turtle Bay Marina just a 5-minute walk away, you have easy access to boat rentals and waterfront dining, making it the perfect base for a memorable group getaway.

Outdoor Features: This waterfront property offers spectacular outdoor spaces, including a rooftop deck with a grill for dinner and a gas firepit for cozy evenings. Multiple balconies provide serene spots to enjoy your morning coffee while taking in the scenic views of the river.

", "about": "

Location: Whiskey Row Retreat is conveniently situated in the West End Park neighborhood, just a short stroll southwest of downtown Nashville. This prime location puts you within walking distance of attractions such as Centennial Park, Vanderbilt University, and a plethora of dining, shopping, and entertainment options. Easy access to major highways and public transportation makes exploring the city effortless.

Outdoor Features: While the property itself doesn't boast outdoor amenities, its proximity to Nashville's attractions ensures you'll have plenty of outdoor activities at your fingertips. Whether it's exploring parks, strolling through vibrant neighborhoods, or attending outdoor events, you'll find endless opportunities to enjoy the fresh air and sunshine.

Indoor Amenities: Step into modern comfort at Whiskey Row Retreat. The interior blends contemporary furnishings with industrial accents, creating spaces that are both stylish and functional. Relax in the living room with plush seating and a smart TV, or whip up a meal in the fully equipped kitchen featuring stainless steel appliances and sleek countertops. High-top stools at the counter offer versatility for dining or entertaining.

Sleeping Arrangements: This home comfortably accommodates up to 4 guests. The private bedroom boasts a luxurious king-size bed adorned with crisp linens, along with a smart TV for entertainment. Additionally, a portable full-size bed provides flexibility for sleeping arrangements.

Important Notes:

  • The condo features a king-size bed in the bedroom and a portable full-size bed.
  • A washer and dryer are conveniently provided within the home.
  • Garage parking is available for 1 vehicle, with additional street parking on a first-come, first-served basis.

Local Attractions: Experience the best of Nashville's attractions within minutes of Whiskey Row Retreat. From catching a game or concert at Bridgestone Arena to exploring Bicentennial State Park, Germantown, and the Capitol Building, there's something for everyone. Don't forget to indulge in Nashville's renowned music scene and nightlife, with Music Row and historic landmarks just a short ride away. Plus, immerse yourself in the city's culinary delights, from finger-lickin' barbecue joints to trendy farm-to-table bistros. The vibrant culture of Music City awaits your exploration!

Interior Amenities: Inside, a cozy atmosphere is created by a stone fireplace extending from the living room to the fully equipped kitchen and lofted game room. The upstairs area offers a pool table, arcade game, and balcony. The living room downstairs features plush couches and a smart TV. {"about": "

Location: Discover the ideal vacation home in Music Row Duo, a combination of two condos – Music City Getaway and Music City Escape. Centrally located, these rentals are under a 10-minute drive or rideshare from downtown Nashville. You'll also be within walking distance of historic Music Row, Vanderbilt University (a 10-minute walk), and the lively 12 South neighborhood. Explore fine dining, designer boutiques, Sevier Park, and iconic murals, all just south of the property.

Outdoor Features: Enjoy the vibrant neighborhood surroundings and outdoor spaces. Music Row Getaway boasts a patio with comfortable seating – a perfect spot for morning coffee or a quiet read.

Indoor Amenities: Step into interiors that offer the comforts of home blended with fresh and modern design elements. Both homes feature spacious living rooms with ample seating and TVs, ideal for relaxation. Stylish kitchens with stainless steel appliances and well-stocked cabinets make meal preparation a breeze. Dining options include seating for 3 at the kitchen island in Music Row Getaway and a high-top table in Music Row Escape.

Sleeping Arrangements: Music Row Getaway comfortably sleeps 5 guests with a private bedroom (king bed), a full-size sleeper sofa, and a twin-over-twin bunk bed in an alcove off the living room. Music Row Escape, similarly accommodating 5 guests, offers a private bedroom (king bed), a full-size sleeper sofa, and a twin-over-twin bunk bed in the first-floor common area.

Important Notes:

  • Laundry facilities are not available in these properties.
  • Street parking, on a first-come, first-served basis, is the available parking option as designated spaces are not provided.

Local Attractions: Explore Nashville's rich cultural offerings within 3 miles of Music Row Duo. Visit downtown for endless shopping, dining, and nightlife, including iconic spots like Ryman Auditorium, the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum, and Music City Walk of Fame Park. Don't miss the lively atmosphere on Broadway Street with honky-tonks and excellent restaurants.

In summary, Music Row Duo offers the perfect blend of private retreat and proximity to Nashville's attractions, making it an ideal choice for a memorable stay in Music City.

Outdoor Features: Enjoy an urban oasis in the spacious, fenced backyard showcasing a sparkling inground pool, shaded pergola, and outdoor seating for lounging or dining al fresco. Host an authentic Tennessee barbecue on the grill as you splash and play the day away, gearing up for an exciting night on the town.

Whether sinking into plush sofas in the living room with a smart TV or enjoying a family movie night by the gas fireplace, the home offers comfort and style.
